In mathematics, the absolute value or modulus |x| of a real number x is the non-negative value of x without regard to its sign.
A notion in mathematics, commonly a number's numerical value without regard to its sign
Magnitude of the number on the real number line

For a real number, its numerical value without regard to its sign; formally, -1 times the number if the number is negative, and the number unmodified if it is zero or positive; the distance of a quantity from zero on a number line.

The magnitude of a number, irrespective of its sign (+ or -). An absolute value is always greater than or equal to zero. For example, 10 is the absolute value of 10 and of -10. Programming languages and spreadsheet programs commonly include functions that return the absolute value of a number.

An anti-lock braking system or anti-skid braking system is an automobile safety system that allows the wheels on a motor vehicle to maintain tractive contact with the road surface according to driver inputs while braking, preventing the wheels from locking up and avoiding uncontrolled skidding.
An electronic automotive safety system for the vehicle braking system
